-- Taiwan Trains Delayed After Earthquake, Transport Ministry Says
-- B y   C i n d y   W a n g
-- 2013-03-27T05:46:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-27/taiwan-trains-delayed-after-earthquake-transport-ministry-says.html
Sixty trains are delayed as of noon
local time after a magnitude 6.1 earthquake struck central
 Taiwan ’s Nantou county at 10:03 a.m., according to the island’s
transport ministry.  The delays are affecting 11,500 travelers, spokesman Veng
Huey-Ping of the Taiwan Railways Administration said by phone
today. The eastern line has resumed normal operations, he said.  The western line between Sanyi, Miaoli County, and Douliou,
Yunlin is still undergoing checks, as is a coastal line between
Tongsiao, Miaoli County, and Douliou, according to Veng. Trains
have slowed to 60 kilometers per hour in these areas.  Douliou is close to the center of earthquake, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cindy Wang in Taipei at 
